<paragraph id="8BF236D3441A233DFF01965CFE50FEE0" blockId="15.[159,1155,332,461]" box="[160,480,332,358]" pageId="15" pageNumber="2853">
<emphasis id="B939EAC1441A233DFF01965CFE50FEE0" bold="true" box="[160,480,332,358]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="2853">Justification of the transfer</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF236D3441A233DFF01967FFB32FE4B" blockId="15.[159,1155,332,461]" pageId="15" pageNumber="2853">
Detailed examination of the 
<typeStatus id="54F68871441A233DFE43967FFDA2FE0E" box="[482,530,367,392]" pageId="15" pageNumber="2853">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D50441A233DFD9D967FFD26FE0E" authorityName="Tikader &amp; Gajbe" authorityYear="1976" box="[572,662,367,392]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Sergiolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="2853" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="singhi">
<emphasis id="B939EAC1441A233DFD9D967FFD26FE0E" box="[572,662,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="2853">S. singhi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
revealed that it lacks diagnostic features of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D50441A233DFF3E9682FF4CFE2D" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1892" box="[159,252,402,427]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Sergiolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="2853" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B939EAC1441A233DFF3E9682FF4CFE2D" box="[159,252,402,427]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="2853">Sergiolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see previous paragraph on 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D50441A233DFDEA9682FC96FE2D" authorityName="Sankaran &amp; Caleb &amp; Sebastian" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Sankaran &amp; Caleb &amp; Sebastian" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[587,806,402,427]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Sergiolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="2853" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lamhetaghatensis">
<emphasis id="B939EAC1441A233DFDEA9682FC96FE2D" box="[587,806,402,427]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="2853">H. lamhetaghatensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), but has all of the diagnostic features of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D50441A233DFEBC96A4FED9FE4B" authorityName="Kamura" authorityYear="1992" box="[285,361,436,461]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Hitobia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="2853" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B939EAC1441A233DFEBC96A4FED9FE4B" box="[285,361,436,461]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="2853">Hitobia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as in the case of previous species (compare 
<figureCitation id="13762A56441A233DFCFD96A4FC08FE4B" box="[860,952,436,461]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="15.[159,224,1645,1668]" captionTargetBox="[166,1150,509,1610]" captionTargetId="figure-87@15.[163,1153,505,1614]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figure 8. Hitobia singhi comb. nov., female holotype of Sergiolus singhi (NZC-ZSI-5052/18). (a) habitus, dorsal view. (b) eyes, dorsal view. (c) epigyne, ventral view. (d) same, dorsal view. (e) label from type bottle. Scale bars a = 2 mm; b = 0.5 mm; c–d = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405205" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405205/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="2853">Figure 8</figureCitation>
(b–d) with Kamura
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF32665B441A233DFF3E917DFD64F939" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405205" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5405205" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405205/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="2853" startId="15.[159,224,1645,1668]" targetBox="[166,1150,509,1610]" targetPageId="15">
<paragraph id="8BF236D3441A233DFF3E917DFD64F939" blockId="15.[159,1157,1645,1727]" pageId="15" pageNumber="2853">
<emphasis id="B939EAC1441A233DFF3E917DFF49F902" bold="true" box="[159,249,1645,1668]" pageId="15" pageNumber="2853">Figure 8.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D50441A233DFF5E917DFE33F902" authorityName="Sankaran &amp; Caleb &amp; Sebastian" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Tikader &amp; Gajbe" baseAuthorityYear="1976" box="[255,387,1645,1668]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Hitobia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="2853" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="singhi" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B939EAC1441A233DFF5E917DFE33F902" box="[255,387,1645,1668]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="2853">Hitobia singhi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20A57BA441A233DFE29917DFE48F902" box="[392,504,1645,1668]" pageId="15" pageNumber="2853" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, female holotype of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D50441A233DFD1F917DFCE2F902" authorityName="Tikader &amp; Gajbe" authorityYear="1976" box="[702,850,1645,1668]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Sergiolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="2853" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="singhi">
<emphasis id="B939EAC1441A233DFD1F917DFCE2F902" box="[702,850,1645,1668]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="2853">Sergiolus singhi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(NZC-ZSI-5052/18). (a) habitus, dorsal view. (b) eyes, dorsal view. (c) epigyne, ventral view. (d) same, dorsal view. (e) label from type bottle. Scale bars a = 2 mm; b = 0.5 mm; c–d = 0.2 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BF236D344052322FF01979EFF42FF4C" blockId="16.[159,1155,142,202]" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854">
1992, figs 11, 16, 20, 25). Based on these observations, we propose to transfer 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D5044052322FBAA979EFBD3FF21" authorityName="Tikader &amp; Gajbe" authorityYear="1976" box="[1035,1123,142,167]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Sergiolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="singhi">
<emphasis id="B939EAC144052322FBAA979EFBD3FF21" box="[1035,1123,142,167]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854">S. singhi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D5044052322FF3E97A1FF5BFF4C" authorityName="Kamura" authorityYear="1992" box="[159,235,177,202]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Hitobia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B939EAC144052322FF3E97A1FF5BFF4C" box="[159,235,177,202]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854">Hitobia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C357655844052322FF0197E6FEC5FC9E" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BF236D344052322FF0197E6FEA4FE96" blockId="16.[160,1156,246,445]" box="[160,276,246,272]" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854">
<emphasis id="B939EAC144052322FF0197E6FEA4FE96" bold="true" box="[160,276,246,272]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF236D344052322FF019609FE0BFE3B" blockId="16.[160,1156,246,445]" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854">
Females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D5044052322FEBC9609FEC9FEB4" authorityName="Sankaran &amp; Caleb &amp; Sebastian" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Sankaran &amp; Caleb &amp; Sebastian" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[285,377,281,306]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Sergiolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="singhi" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B939EAC144052322FEBC9609FEC9FEB4" box="[285,377,281,306]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854">H. singhi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20A57BA44052322FEDF9609FE4AFEB4" box="[382,506,281,306]" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
seem closely related to the females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D5044052322FC039609FB88FEB4" authorityName="Sankaran &amp; Caleb &amp; Sebastian" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Sankaran &amp; Caleb &amp; Sebastian" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[930,1080,281,306]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Sergiolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="poonaensis" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B939EAC144052322FC039609FB88FEB4" box="[930,1080,281,306]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854">H. poonaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20A57BA44052322FB9F9609FF61FED3" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in the shape of spermathecae, but can be distinguished from the latter by epigyne without anterior hood (which is present in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D5044052322FD10964EFCFFFEF1" authorityName="Sankaran &amp; Caleb &amp; Sebastian" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Sankaran &amp; Caleb &amp; Sebastian" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[689,847,350,375]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Sergiolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="poonaensis">
<emphasis id="B939EAC144052322FD10964EFCFFFEF1" box="[689,847,350,375]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854">H. poonaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and epigynal plate with V-shaped posterior margin (which is crescent-like in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D5044052322FCA29691FC2DFE1C" authorityName="Sankaran &amp; Caleb &amp; Sebastian" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Sankaran &amp; Caleb &amp; Sebastian" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[771,925,385,410]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Sergiolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="poonaensis">
<emphasis id="B939EAC144052322FCA29691FC2DFE1C" box="[771,925,385,410]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854">H. poonaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (compare 
<figureCitation id="13762A5644052322FB859691FB33FE1C" box="[1060,1155,385,410]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="12.[160,225,1408,1431]" captionTargetBox="[166,1149,145,1373]" captionTargetId="figure-49@12.[163,1153,142,1376]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 7. Hitobia poonaensis comb. nov., male allotype and female holotype (NZC-ZSI-5049/18) of Sergiolus poonaensis. (a–c) left pedipalp of allotype male: (a) ventral view. (b) ventro-retrolateral view. (c) retrolateral tibial apophysis, retrolateral view. (d–e) epigyne of holotype female: (d) ventral view. (e) dorsal view. Abbreviations: C, conductor; E, embolus; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; TA, tegular apophysis; TP, tegular process; VPT, apico-ventral process of tibia. Scale bars a–e = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405203" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405203/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854">Figure 7</figureCitation>
(d–e) with 
<figureCitation id="13762A5644052322FEB896B4FEC7FE3B" box="[281,375,420,445]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="15.[159,224,1645,1668]" captionTargetBox="[166,1150,509,1610]" captionTargetId="figure-87@15.[163,1153,505,1614]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figure 8. Hitobia singhi comb. nov., female holotype of Sergiolus singhi (NZC-ZSI-5052/18). (a) habitus, dorsal view. (b) eyes, dorsal view. (c) epigyne, ventral view. (d) same, dorsal view. (e) label from type bottle. Scale bars a = 2 mm; b = 0.5 mm; c–d = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405205" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405205/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854">Figure 8</figureCitation>
(c–d)).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF236D344052322FF0196F8FE6EFD84" blockId="16.[160,1156,488,792]" box="[160,478,488,514]" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854">
<emphasis id="B939EAC144052322FF0196F8FE6EFD84" bold="true" box="[160,478,488,514]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854">Supplementary description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF236D344052322FF01951CFD63FD73" blockId="16.[160,1156,488,792]" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854">
Female (
<typeStatus id="54F6887144052322FEA2951CFEDBFDA3" box="[259,363,524,549]" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854">holotype</typeStatus>
, 
<figureCitation id="13762A5644052322FED8951CFE6AFDA3" box="[377,474,524,549]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="15.[159,224,1645,1668]" captionTargetBox="[166,1150,509,1610]" captionTargetId="figure-87@15.[163,1153,505,1614]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figure 8. Hitobia singhi comb. nov., female holotype of Sergiolus singhi (NZC-ZSI-5052/18). (a) habitus, dorsal view. (b) eyes, dorsal view. (c) epigyne, ventral view. (d) same, dorsal view. (e) label from type bottle. Scale bars a = 2 mm; b = 0.5 mm; c–d = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405205" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405205/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854">Figure 8</figureCitation>
(a–b)). Body length 9.44. Prosoma length 3.42, width 2.72. Opisthosoma length 6.02, width 3.72. Eye sizes and interdistances: ALE 0.13. AME 0.12. PLE 0.14. PME 0.11; AME–AME 0.12. AME–PME 0.20. PME–PLE 0.16. PME–PME 0.15. Length of chelicerae 1.05. Clypeus height at ALEs 0.12, at AMEs 0.15. 
<emphasis id="B939EAC144052322FCD29564FC78FD0B" box="[883,968,628,653]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854">Epigyne</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13762A5644052322FC7D9564FBF0FD0B" box="[988,1088,628,653]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="15.[159,224,1645,1668]" captionTargetBox="[166,1150,509,1610]" captionTargetId="figure-87@15.[163,1153,505,1614]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figure 8. Hitobia singhi comb. nov., female holotype of Sergiolus singhi (NZC-ZSI-5052/18). (a) habitus, dorsal view. (b) eyes, dorsal view. (c) epigyne, ventral view. (d) same, dorsal view. (e) label from type bottle. Scale bars a = 2 mm; b = 0.5 mm; c–d = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405205" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405205/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854">Figure 8</figureCitation>
(c–d)): epigynal plate sclerotised, with V-shaped posterior epigynal margin (
<figureCitation id="13762A5644052322FC549587FBEBFD36" box="[1013,1115,663,688]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="15.[159,224,1645,1668]" captionTargetBox="[166,1150,509,1610]" captionTargetId="figure-87@15.[163,1153,505,1614]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figure 8. Hitobia singhi comb. nov., female holotype of Sergiolus singhi (NZC-ZSI-5052/18). (a) habitus, dorsal view. (b) eyes, dorsal view. (c) epigyne, ventral view. (d) same, dorsal view. (e) label from type bottle. Scale bars a = 2 mm; b = 0.5 mm; c–d = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405205" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405205/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854">Figure 8</figureCitation>
(c)). Copulatory openings small, lying distantly from each other. Spermathecae large sac-like. (
<figureCitation id="13762A5644052322FF0995CCFEB5FD73" box="[168,261,732,757]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="15.[159,224,1645,1668]" captionTargetBox="[166,1150,509,1610]" captionTargetId="figure-87@15.[163,1153,505,1614]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figure 8. Hitobia singhi comb. nov., female holotype of Sergiolus singhi (NZC-ZSI-5052/18). (a) habitus, dorsal view. (b) eyes, dorsal view. (c) epigyne, ventral view. (d) same, dorsal view. (e) label from type bottle. Scale bars a = 2 mm; b = 0.5 mm; c–d = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405205" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405205/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854">Figure 8</figureCitation>
(d)). Fertilisation ducts narrow, diverging.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF236D344052322FF6195EFFEC5FC9E" blockId="16.[160,1156,488,792]" box="[192,373,767,792]" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854">
<emphasis id="B939EAC144052322FF6195EFFF45FC9E" box="[192,245,767,792]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854">Male</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C357655844052322FF019453FE0DFBAB" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF236D344052322FF019453FEB6FCDB" blockId="16.[160,1156,835,1069]" box="[160,262,835,861]" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854">
<emphasis id="B939EAC144052322FF019453FEB6FCDB" bold="true" box="[160,262,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF236D344052322FF019477FE0DFBAB" blockId="16.[160,1156,835,1069]" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854">
The ZSI collection has one glass bottle for this species labelled as ‘holotype’ (5052/18) containing a female specimen in poor condition. The same bottle has a small glass vial containing the dissected epigyne. 
<materialsCitation id="3B253C8E44052322FD8494BCFBDAFC6E" collectionCode="V" collectorName="There" location="Maharashtra" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Maharashtra">
<collectorName id="26B8530544052322FD8494BCFDD4FC43" box="[549,612,940,965]" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854">There</collectorName>
is a glass bottle in the ZSI collection containing a female specimen (4017/18) in poor condition collected from 
<collectingRegion id="4989F83144052322FC3794DFFB91FC6E" box="[918,1057,975,1000]" country="India" name="Maharashtra" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854">Maharashtra</collectingRegion>
by 
<collectionCode id="ED5CAE1644052322FBF694DFFBDAFC6E" box="[1111,1130,975,1000]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
</materialsCitation>
.D. Srivastava on 
<date id="FFF3101344052322FEF094E1FD9CFB8C" box="[337,556,1009,1034]" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854" value="1970-02-10">10 February 1970</date>
. It is misidentified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D5044052322FCF394E1FC07FB8C" authorityName="Sankaran &amp; Caleb &amp; Sebastian" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Sankaran &amp; Caleb &amp; Sebastian" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[850,951,1009,1034]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Sergiolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="singhi">
<emphasis id="B939EAC144052322FCF394E1FC07FB8C" box="[850,951,1009,1034]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854">S. singhi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is, in fact, 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D5044052322FF019304FE88FBAB" authorityName="Sankaran &amp; Caleb &amp; Sebastian" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Sankaran &amp; Caleb &amp; Sebastian" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[160,312,1044,1069]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Sergiolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="poonaensis" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B939EAC144052322FF019304FE88FBAB" box="[160,312,1044,1069]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854">H. poonaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20A57BA44052322FEE19304FE0DFBAB" box="[320,445,1044,1069]" pageId="16" pageNumber="2854" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
